{meta: title In The Hills Of Shiloh}
{meta: artist Bobby Bare}
{meta: composer Shel Silverstein}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Have you seen [F]Amanda [C]Blaine
[A]In the Hills of [C]Shiloh
[F]Wandering through the morning [C]rain
[A]In the Hills of [C]Shiloh
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[F]Have you seen her at her [C]door
[F]Listening for the cannon [C]roar
[F]And the man who went to [C]war
[A]From the Hills of [C]Shiloh
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]Have you heard her mournful [C]cries
[A]In the Hills of [C]Shiloh
[F]Have you seen her haunted [C]eyes
[A]In the Hills of [C]Shiloh
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[F]Have you seen her running [C]down
[F]Searching through the sleepy [C]town
[F]In her yellowed wedding [C]gown
[A]In the Hills of [C]Shiloh
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[F]Have you seen her standing [C]there
[A]In the Hills of [C]Shiloh
[F]Wind a blowing through her [C]hair
[A]In the Hills of [C]Shiloh
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
[F]Listening for the sound of [C]guns
[F]Listening for the rolling [C]drums
[F]And the man who never [C]comes
[A]To the Hills of [C]Shiloh
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 7}
[F]Have you heard Amanda [C]sing
[A]In the Hills of [C]Shiloh
[F]Whispering to her wedding [C]ring
[A]In the Hills of [C]Shiloh
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 8}
[F]Hear her humming soft and [C]low
[F]Poor Amanda doesn't [C]know
[F]Twas ended forty years [C]ago
[A]In the Hills of [C]Shiloh
{end_of_verse}
